<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-1585] SFTP GenericFileProducer.createFileName produces OS normalized file name, that doesn&apos;t work with SFTP</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1585</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The use of File.separator and FileUtil.normalizePath in GenericFileProducer.createFileName produce a OS normalized file name, that doesn&apos;t work with SFTP&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g. outbound&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;out_20090501_091940_ACC.txt which will not work produce a file called outboundout_20090501_091940_ACC.txt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The proper name should be outbound/out_20090501_091940_ACC.txt&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12486058">CAMEL-1585</key>
